1 (b) The offense was possession of marijuana and the conviction was prior to January 1, 1972.
2 (4) Subsection (1) of this section does not apply to any person who has been:
3 (a) Convicted of only one felony under the law of this state or any other state, or who has been
4 convicted of only one felony under the laws of the United States, which felony did not involve
5 criminal homicide, as defined in ORS 163.005, or the possession or use of a firearm or a weapon
6 having a blade that projects or swings into position by force of a spring or by centrifugal force, and
7 who has been discharged from imprisonment, parole or probation for said offense for a period of 15
8 years prior to the date of alleged violation of subsection (1) of this section; or
9 (b) Granted relief from the disability under 18 U.S.C. 925(c) or ORS 166.274 or has had the
10 person’s record expunged under the laws of this state or equivalent laws of another jurisdiction.
11 (5)(a) Felon in possession of a firearm is a Class C felony.
12 (b) Aggravated felon in possession of a firearm is a Class B felony.
13 (c) Felon in possession of a restricted weapon is a Class A misdemeanor.
14 (6)(a) Except as provided in paragraph (b) of this subsection, the Oregon Criminal Justice
15 Commission shall classify aggravated felon in possession of a firearm as crime category 7
16 of the sentencing guidelines grid of the commission.
17 (b) The commission shall classify aggravated felon in possession of a firearm as crime
18 category 8 if the person:
19 (A) Owns or has in the person’s possession, or under the person’s custody or control, six
20 or more firearms; or
21 (B) At the time of the offense, has three or more prior convictions under subsection (1)
22 of this section.
